{"word":"φθιτός","slug":"φθιτός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φθιτός</b></el> <el>(φθῐτός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <el>φθίνω</el>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b> word, only used in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>φθιτοί</el> always without the <a href='S:Article'>Art.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>the dead</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>liable to perish</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}